  "source_notes": "Sy Scholfield quotes him in an interview:\\nCaro De Robertis: Where maybe some of these insights came in a hard one-way. Can you say when and where you were born?\\nVincent Crisostomo: Okay, I was born in Tachikawa, Japan, which is a US air force base outside of Tokyo. And I know this, because I had to do—I was doing my chart, I think I was born at 6:05 in the morning, and I'm an Aquarius with an Aquarius moon. So, double Aquarian. Yes, so my mother often jokes that we were \"made in Japan.\"\\n(\"Vincent Crisostomo, AIDS activist and LGBTQ+ rights advocate,\" Elders Project, Columbia University [https://eldersproject.incite.columbia.edu/interviews/vincent-crisostomo]).\\nBirth date from Alchetron.com (\"Born February 6, 1961 (age 64) (1961-02-06 ) Tachikawa, Japan\") [https://alchetron.com/Vincent-Crisostomo].\\nThis date gives him Aquarius Sun and Aquarius Ascendant (and thereby a Double Aquarius) with Moon in Libra.\\n",
